      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STORMY DAY (1) boasts a strong record this journey with five wins and four minors from 10 tries. Was out of placings last time (22.41) at Murray Bridge in a Grade 3/4/5, finishing fourth and beaten 5.5 lengths. Looks a leading chance on best. GIN AND JUICE (4) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at Gawler in a handy 22.92 beating Chalupa Batman. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Can continue on with his winning form. CRAZED (2) turned in a solid run last start over 400m at Bulli finishing 5th and beaten only 5 lengths (22.60). The form out of last race has been strong. Should be about the money. RED SAID SO (8) has ability and looks a top-three prospect.",
